Class FlowVolumeUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentrafficsim.core.unit.Unit<FlowVolumeUnit>
      • org.opentrafficsim.core.unit.FlowVolumeUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class FlowVolumeUnit
extends Unit<FlowVolumeUnit>
    The volume flow rate is the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit of time (wikipedia).

        public FlowVolumeUnit(LengthUnit lengthUnit,
              TimeUnit timeUnit,
              String nameKey,
              String abbreviationKey,
              UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Create a flow-volumeunit based on length (cubed) per time unit.
        Parameters:
        lengthUnit - the unit of length for the flow unit, e.g., meter
        timeUnit - the unit of time for the flow unit, e.g., second
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial

              String nameKey,
              String abbreviationKey,
              UnitSystem unitSystem)
        Create a flow-volumeunit based as a volume unit per time unit.
        Parameters:
        volumeUnit - the unit of volume for the flow unit, e.g., cubic meter
        timeUnit - the unit of time for the flow unit, e.g., second
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial

      • FlowVolumeUnit

        public FlowVolumeUnit(String nameKey,
              String abbreviationKey,
              UnitSystem unitSystem,
              FlowVolumeUnit referenceUnit,
              double conversionFactorToReferenceUnit)
        Create a flow-volumeunit based on another flow-volumeunit.
        Parameters:
        nameKey - the key to the locale file for the long name of the unit
        abbreviationKey - the key to the locale file for the abbreviation of the unit
        unitSystem - the unit system, e.g. SI or Imperial
        referenceUnit - the unit to convert to
        conversionFactorToReferenceUnit - multiply a value in this unit by the factor to convert to the given reference unit
